  "body": "### Description of the Issue\r\n\r\nCurrently, we don't really have a standard for how we write inputs or how they're displayed. Since the inputs were last updated, we've added a few new types of input: inputs with searchable dropdowns, multi column dropdowns, and a few general changes to all input types. To maintain consistent styles across all input types, and to make abstraction easier, it's time to update how we write our `<Input />` components.\r\n\r\n### Proposed Changes\r\n\r\n- develop a consistent style for all input types\r\n- provide a consistent method for adding inline error messages to all input types\r\n- encapsulate all input types into into individual components for ease of use\r\n\t- i.e. `<Input {...props} />`, `<InlineDropdown {...props} />`, `<SearchDropdown {...props} />`, `<InlineMsg {...props} />`, etc...\r\n- standardize all error messages, and displayed them consistently across all inputs\r\n\t- error messages should be displayed inline, __not__ displayed via notification bar\r\n\t- example: <img width=\"726\" alt=\"screen shot 2018-05-01 at 3 29 20 pm\" src=\"https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/7861465/39492197-721d5986-4d54-11e8-9e72-9b7cdb814941.png\">\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n",
